{"sourceChecksum": "90436025acd77acc68c20a760ef23995c84fc550c9bc6015179179b681ca4df6", "levels": {"l1": {"summaryText": "Invasive ductal carcinoma, grade 2, stage IIB.", "generatedTime": "2025-05-05 07:03:39.868242", "metadata": {"model": "gpt-4o", "modelVersion": "2024-05-13", "promptId": "ONCO_RES_SUMMARY_L1_PROMPT", "promptVersion": "1"}}, "l2": {"summaryText": "Patient Name: Maria Gonzalez, a 59-year-old female, presented with a suspicious mass in the upper outer quadrant of the left breast. There is evidence of lymphovascular invasion and surrounding ductal carcinoma in situ (DCIS), with no significant involvement of the skin or chest wall.
